# skill: startblock

## Purpose
Executed at the start of every new block. Establishes context, reads current state, confirms scope.

## Steps
1. Read `meta/activeContext.md` — confirm current block and last completed block.
2. Read `.agents/rules/` — load all active rules before writing any code.
3. Confirm with user: "I'm about to start Block [X]. Scope: [Y]. Proceed?"
4. Do NOT write any code until scope is confirmed.
5. After completing the block, update `meta/activeContext.md` BLOCK HISTORY and commit.